USAir Group Inc said it hasacquired 2,292,599 Piedmont Aviation Inc shares, about 9.9 pcton a fully diluted basis, from Norfolk Southern Corp &lt;NSC>.    The acquisition of Piedmont by USAir has been approved bythe directors of both companies.    USAir said it has been advised by Norfolk Southern that thecompany supports the proposed merger and intends to tender allof its remaining 1,477,829 Piedmont common shares in responseto USAir's tender offer which began today. This total includesshares issuable upon conversion of Piedmont preferred, USAirnoted.    USAir said Piedmont has about 23.1 mln common shares on afully diluted basis, adding its offer is conditioned on thetender of at least 9,309,394 shares, representing 40.2 pct ofthe oustanding shares on a diluted basis.    USAir said the 3,491,030 new shares it has an option to buyrepresent 18.5 pct of Piedmont's currently outstanding shares. Reuter&#3;